HEADWORD: Old Line State
<hw>Old Line State</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>Maryland; a nickname,
alluding to the fact that its northern boundary is Mason and Dixon's
line.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>old-maidish</ent>⟦br⟧
